description.narrative: Countries have relevant knowledge and data to design evidence-based, results-based child protection programmes for improved child protection outcomes for children, adolescents and women., which contributes to Access To Justice, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation By 2021, UNICEF supported countries apply relevant policies, innovative approaches and evidence, to design and implement publicly and privately funded development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that Protect Every Child from Violence and Exploitation
